    {
      "id": "uu80_qlseyjXhX6TrRlV0",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1173.5873015873017,
      "y": 1036.888888888889,
      "width": 429,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "ap",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 824984755,
      "version": 72,
      "versionNonce": 106159869,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783534039222,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Kent Beck's Four Rules of Simple Design",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Kent Beck's Four Rules of Simple Design",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "66xBLcGDYuCw_hDHFlFru",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 333.5873015873017,
      "y": 1716.8888888888887,
      "width": 1386,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aq",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1901651827,
      "version": 521,
      "versionNonce": 357075965,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783534976990,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Why is code duplication bad:\n    - if it isn't a named first class thing, it's hard to find out where the problem is happening.\n    - if it needs to be changed, you have to change it in multiple places. (#1 first answer you should give)\n        - but will you though?\n        - but what if you change it in a centralized place to fix your localized problem, but that actually breaks other uses?\n\n    - \"poor use of resources\" - \"we already paid you to write that code once!\" \n    ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Why is code duplication bad:\n    - if it isn't a named first class thing, it's hard to find out where the problem is happening.\n    - if it needs to be changed, you have to change it in multiple places. (#1 first answer you should give)\n        - but will you though?\n        - but what if you change it in a centralized place to fix your localized problem, but that actually breaks other uses?\n\n    - \"poor use of resources\" - \"we already paid you to write that code once!\" \n    ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "HGjIZnSKK-V-lPZwm9G7X",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 385.0158730158731,
      "y": 2046.8888888888891,
      "width": 1122,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "ar",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 704301661,
      "version": 171,
      "versionNonce": 733832733,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783534901961,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Removing duplication is generalizing code. \"What works for me should work for every use of this thing\"\n    - now and in the future\n    - HIGH bar. ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Removing duplication is generalizing code. \"What works for me should work for every use of this thing\"\n    - now and in the future\n    - HIGH bar. ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "3eSj5hVE2ISobZYi-VzD3",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 390.7301587301589,
      "y": 2216.888888888889,
      "width": 550,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "as",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1928585021,
      "version": 54,
      "versionNonce": 2004790045,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783534953990,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\"Premature generalization is the root of all evil\"",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\"Premature generalization is the root of all evil\"",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "kCObd2WZoQd4K2DI8ja1p",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 439.30158730158746,
      "y": 2334.0317460317465,
      "width": 1188,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "at",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 72067699,
      "version": 193,
      "versionNonce": 1837785715,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783535126719,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Code has to be duplicated at least three times (my code that i'm writing) before I'll consider generalizing.\n    - Jeff\nDan North (Behavior Driven Development) - RUG - \"Repeat until good\".",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Code has to be duplicated at least three times (my code that i'm writing) before I'll consider generalizing.\n    - Jeff\nDan North (Behavior Driven Development) - RUG - \"Repeat until good\".",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "G4-RpGyByt9FNuOEGAy1w",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 419.30158730158746,
      "y": 2522.603174603175,
      "width": 1298,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "au",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 161215315,
      "version": 256,
      "versionNonce": 218120627,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783535204161,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "It is REALLY hard to \"kill your children\" - code that you put a lot of effort into is makes it hard to see its faults.\n\"It has to be me, not the code\" - make your code disposable until it earns its keep. \n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "It is REALLY hard to \"kill your children\" - code that you put a lot of effort into is makes it hard to see its faults.\n\"It has to be me, not the code\" - make your code disposable until it earns its keep. \n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "6KTVBLvbcLVu1EVV-ekkK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 554.5,
      "y": 2924,
      "width": 1316.8193359375,
      "height": 325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "av",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 917409966,
      "version": 396,
      "versionNonce": 1584232814,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1783605144225,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Every day your code isn't in production the company is losing money.\n\n\nTDD - FANTASTIC - as a design tool. \n- You aren't always designing stuff, though.\n\nTest First - My way of doing things *most of the time*:\n    - System Test \n        - Unit Tests as needed\n            - Unit Integration Tests (a test that doesn't fully demonstrate capability, but it uses a network, filesystem, databse, etc.)\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Every day your code isn't in production the company is losing money.\n\n\nTDD - FANTASTIC - as a design tool. \n- You aren't always designing stuff, though.\n\nTest First - My way of doing things *most of the time*:\n    - System Test \n        - Unit Tests as needed\n            - Unit Integration Tests (a test that doesn't fully demonstrate capability, but it uses a network, filesystem, databse, etc.)\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
